      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to the linear elastic solver kernel. Patch tests and single-element benchmarks confirm correct element formulation. Convergence order matches theoretical prediction for hexahedral elements. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study required; achieved level must equal required level 3.",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study performed across three mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine). Richardson extrapolation applied; discretization error in peak von Mises stress estimated at 1.8%, within the 5% acceptance threshold. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
