      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection justified against experimental data; achieved level must equal required level 3.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic isotropic constitutive model appropriate for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) under quasi-static loading below yield. Contact formulation (augmented Lagrangian) validated against analytical Hertzian contact benchmarks. Model form uncertainty quantified via sensitivity analysis. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometry sourced from traceable measurements; achieved level must equal required level 3.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa) and Poisson's ratio (0.34) sourced from ASTM E8 coupon tests on implant-grade Ti-6Al-4V lot material. CAD geometry verified against CMM measurements of production screws with tolerances within 0.05 mm. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
